    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) that stands as a testament to meticulous preservation. The M96/03 3.6L flat-six power plant features the VarioCam Plus system for optimized valve timing and lift, delivering a linear torque curve and seamless throttle response. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle remains precise, with no synchro wear or linkage play. This example boasts a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a bone-dry undercarriage, free of rear main seal concerns. The suspension geometry is factory-spec, utilizing MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear setup for superior lateral grip and composure. The braking system retains its four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors with zero thermal stress cracking. Finished in its original paint with zero imperfections, the car retains its factory-applied cosmoline and pristine interior upholstery. A museum-grade specimen for the serious enthusiast.",
